{"session_id":"e4abc67f-acfb-4c6b-814f-6a86b17af140","transcript_path":"/Users/jinayoon/.claude/projects/-Users-jinayoon-HogTTV/e4abc67f-acfb-4c6b-814f-6a86b17af140.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/jinayoon/HogTTV","permission_mode":"acceptEdits","effort":{"level":"high"},"hook_event_name":"Stop","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"The extension is fully built. Here's the status and next steps:\n\n---\n\n## What's built\n\nAll the core functionality is done:\n- **Popup** — enter your Slack token, sync emojis, view cache status\n- **Background service worker** — fetches `emoji.list` from Slack API, resolves aliases, caches for 4h\n- **Content script** — injects a `🏷` picker button into Meet's chat input, renders `:emoji_name:` shortcodes in received messages as images\n\n---\n\n## How to load it locally in Chrome\n\n1. Open `chrome://extensions` in Chrome\n2. Toggle **Developer mode** on (top-right)\n3. Click **Load unpacked**\n4. Select the `/Users/jinayoon/HogTTV` folder\n5. The extension icon should appear in your toolbar\n\n---\n\n## How to get a Slack token to test with\n\n1. Go to [api.slack.com/apps](https://api.slack.com/apps) → **Create New App** → From scratch\n2. Under **OAuth & Permissions** → **User Token Scopes** → add `emoji:read`\n3. **Install to workspace** → copy the **User OAuth Token** (starts with `xoxp-`)\n\nThen: click the extension icon → paste the token → **Sync emojis** → you should see a count of custom emojis cached.\n\n---\n\n## How to test in Meet\n\n1. Join any Google Meet (even a solo call works: [meet.new](https://meet.new))\n2. Open the chat panel\n3. Look for a `🏷` button next to the chat input — click it to open the picker\n4. Search for an emoji name and click it — it should insert `:emoji_name: ` into the input\n\n---\n\n## What could come next\n\nThe main gap right now is **Meet's chat input selectors may not match** — Google Meet's DOM changes often. If the `🏷` button doesn't appear, that's the first thing to debug (open DevTools on meet.google.com and check which selector the chat textarea actually has)."}

