{"session_id":"e50dcf12-88bc-4372-b7bd-f9a15cd35e8b","transcript_path":"/Users/jinayoon/.claude/projects/-Users-jinayoon-HogTTV/e50dcf12-88bc-4372-b7bd-f9a15cd35e8b.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/jinayoon/HogTTV","permission_mode":"acceptEdits","effort":{"level":"high"},"hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"cat <<'EOF' | /Users/jinayoon/HogTTV/hoggit-aarch64-apple-darwin/hoggit intent capture -m claude-sonnet-4-6\nFix bug where only the most recent custom emoji renders in chat\n\nRoot cause: PROCESSED_ATTR (data-slack-emoji-rendered) was set on the parent\nelement of a processed text node to prevent re-processing. But when Google Meet\nsends a new message, it updates the DOM — the parent of the first message may\nretain the PROCESSED_ATTR attribute even after Meet refreshes its text content\nback to the raw shortcode (e.g. :bufo-alarma:). The TreeWalker then rejects\nthat text node via the closest() check, leaving the first emoji as plain text\nwhile only processing the new message.\n\nFix: remove the PROCESSED_ATTR guard entirely. The walker already won't revisit\nprocessed nodes because those text nodes are replaced with <img> elements and\nthe shortcode pattern won't match image elements. If Meet refreshes text content,\nwe want to re-render it anyway.\nEOF","description":"Capture hoggit intent for this fix"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D912dnVh1oEimApUT5WNtY"}

